benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/allCustomFields - Retrieve account customFields

covered: Valid GET requests for account custom fields are covered by multiple scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC05, TC06, TC07, TC08, TC09, TC12, TC13, TC14, TC15, TC16, TC17, TC18, TC21, TC22, TC24, TC25, TC26, TC27, TC28, TC29, TC30, TC31, TC32, TC33, TC34, TC35, TC36, TC37, TC38, TC39).
Edge cases for input validation including invalid accountId formats, whitespace, extremely long IDs, missing fields, and invalid objectType values (TC12, TC17, TC18, TC32, TC33, TC34, TC35, TC36).
Authorization and authentication scenarios covered: missing token and invalid token (TC14, TC15); service outage and integration failures (TC16, TC23).
Regression tests for audit handling and backward compatibility (TC21, TC22, TC39).
Performance and scalability scenarios (TC11, TC25, TC26).
Data integrity and cross-service consistency checks (TC24).
Accessibility considerations and descriptive error messages (TC37, TC38).
gaps: Pagination handling for large datasets is not tested.
Caching behavior and headers (ETag, Cache-Control) are not tested.
Rate limiting/throttling behavior is not tested.
Explicit 403 Unauthorized (insufficient permissions) scenarios are not covered (only 401 for missing/invalid tokens).
Internal server error (500) scenarios beyond service availability are not tested.
recommendations: Add a dedicated pagination test to verify page, limit, and total count handling for large result sets.
Add tests for 403 responses when authenticated but lacking permissions, and 500 tests for server-side failures.
Add tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and potential cache invalidation.
Add rate-limiting tests to ensure proper handling of bursts of requests.
Consider consolidating common setup/teardown to reduce test fragility and improve maintainability.
